**Job Description:**

**About DXC**

DXC Technology is the world’s leading independent, end-to-end IT services company, helping clients harness the power of innovation to thrive on change. We help our customers across the entire Enterprise Technology Stack with differentiated industry solutions. We modernize IT, optimize data architectures, and make everything secure, scalable and orchestrated across public, private and hybrid clouds. DXC is an employer of choice with strong values, and fosters a culture of inclusion, belonging and corporate citizenship.


We are now looking for an IT Legal Counsel to join our Team!


This role would be ideal for candidates who strive for excellence when getting things done, whilst continuously seeking new and improved ways of impacting our day-to-day operations. If you are inquisitive and you are not easily intimidated by ambiguity and ever-changing requirements, this is the place to be.


**Daily challenges**

* Draft, review and negotiate various types of customer contracts and contractual documents;
* Provide ongoing advice to the Account teams regarding the legal and commercial implications of specific contract terms and conditions, including analyzing, drafting and reviewing IT contracts with respect to contract and commercial activities;
* Working closely with DXC's pursuit teams and internal stakeholders on RFPs and new business opportunities;
* Perform legal, administrative, and operational research to support the proposal and contract development;
* Maintain deadlines on deliverables and communicate on an ongoing basis with business partners and internal clients about contractual issues;
* Guiding DXC's managers and ensure compliance with rules and regulations;
* Develop DXC's positions on various legal matters.

**Experience and skills required**

* Master`s degree in Law in IT/IP/contract
* Professional Fluency in Swedish and English;
* 7+ years’ experience in a law firm and/or global corporation.
* Outsourcing/supplier experience would be considered an advantage;
* Good understanding of the contractual and commercial risks/issues in transactions;
* Good working knowledge of the fundamental legal provisions of commercial contracts;
* Ability to provide guidance/interpretation on existing contract provisions.
* Position based in Stockholm, Sweden. This is a hybrid role, normally requiring 1-2 days a week at the office.

We Deliver eXcellence for our Customers and colleagues every day. Our values form the foundation of everything we do and every decision we make.


If you see yourself working with us, do not hesitate sending us your CV in English.


At DXC Technology, we believe strong connections and community are key to our success. Our work model prioritizes in-person collaboration while offering flexibility to support wellbeing, productivity, individual work styles, and life circumstances. We’re committed to fostering an inclusive environment where everyone can thrive.


**Recruitment fraud is a scheme in which fictitious job opportunities are offered to job seekers typically through online services, such as false websites, or through unsolicited emails claiming to be from the company. These emails may request recipients to provide personal information or to make payments as part of their illegitimate recruiting process. DXC does not make offers of employment via social media networks and DXC never asks for any money or payments from applicants at any point in the recruitment process, nor ask a job seeker to purchase IT or other equipment on our behalf.**
